genresAdvancedInfo.name: italo house
genresAdvancedInfo.description: A subgenre of house music that originated in Italy in the late 1980s and early 1990s. Italo house is known for its high-energy beats, uplifting melodies, and soulful vocals. The genre combines elements of disco, funk, and electronic music, and is often characterized by its use of piano riffs, brass stabs, and gospel-inspired vocals.
